@NotSoSpooky It is no that easy. You see man was created by evolution and is still subject to its laws. In particular, such an evolutionarily sensitive area as sexual and reproductive behavior is strictly under the control of instincts and conscious responses have virtually no influence on it.

Hence, particular sexual habits, taboos, prohibitions and orders are not a matter of chance, but are evolutionarily conditioned. Society tolerates certain sexual behavior as long as it does not detract from its evolutionary fitness. It does not tolerate those that reduce it. 

In other worlds society hatred towards incest is not something consciously calculated. It is a purely instinctive, hormonal, genetically controlled, evolutionary response.
